-- Peru Stocks: Candente, Credicorp, Rio Alto, Southern Copper Rise
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2011-12-23T21:27:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-23/peru-stocks-candente-credicorp-rio-alto-southern-copper-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of today’s close.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.2 percent to 19,428.81. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index  gained 0.4 percent to 2,526.14.  Mining companies advanced after copper rose on signs that
U.S. economic growth may spur demand for industrial metals.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , the Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, jumped the most in
six weeks, climbing 11 percent to 98 cents.  Rio Cristal
Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian exploration company,
climbed 11 percent to 10 cents.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a
gold producer, rose 1.9 percent to $3.18.  Southern Copper Corp. 
(SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper producer, gained 1 percent to
$30.85.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, advanced 1.1 percent to $108.14, after U.S. stocks
rose.  To contact the reporter on this story:
